Present Constitution (Const. Art. VI, §5) authorizes a local governmental subdivision to
draft, adopt, or amend a home rule charter. Provides the governing authority of a local
subdivision may appoint a commission to prepare and propose a charter or an alternate
charter, or may call an election to elect such a commission. Provides for the method of
approving or amending a home rule charter. Provides for the adoption of a home rule charter
by two or more local governmental subdivisions. Provides for the structure, organization,
powers, and functions of a local governmental subdivision that has adopted a home rule
charter.
Proposed constitutional amendment retains present constitution.
Present constitution provides that a home rule charter or other plan of government shall not
contain provisions that affect a school board or the offices of district attorney, sheriff,
assessor, clerk of a district court, or coroner, which is inconsistent with present constitution.
Proposed constitutional amendment provides that a home rule charter or other plan of
government may authorize a local ethics entity to audit or investigate a school board or the
offices of district attorney, sheriff, assessor, clerk of a district court, or coroner.
Present constitution (Const Art. VI, §6) prohibits the legislature from enacting a law the
effect of which changes or affects the structure and organization or the particular distribution
and redistribution of the powers and functions of any local governmental subdivision which
operates under a home rule charter.
Proposed constitutional amendment provides that present constitution does not prohibit the
legislature relating to local ethics entities.
Provides for submission of the proposed amendment to the voters at the statewide election
to be held November 3, 2026.
(Amends Const. Art. VI, §§5(G) and 6)
